Sisa Canca, News24 (iStock) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Johannesburg - Eight people were arrested for public violence during a protest in Mzimhlophe, Soweto, on Monday, Gauteng police said.They would appear in court soon, Captain Kay Makhubela said. A ninth person ran away during the arrests.Protesters had barricaded the Soweto Highway since 03:00 on Thursday, in a protest against evictions in the area.&nbsp; &nbsp;Makhubela said Johannesburg metro police chased them away as they were advancing on a Metrorail train station in the area. Broadcaster eNCA reported that signalling infrastructure on the Naledi-Johannesburg line was damaged.24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.